"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=2AE037D3-6705-43B5-828C-C117387FADDD&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fstate-department-orders-partial-evacuation-of-u-s-embassy-in-niger-48bcb7bd&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">尼日尔上周发生政变后，欧洲各国政府和美国下令从尼日尔撤离本国公民。 The leader of the junta said the military won&#39;t bow to pressure to reinstate ousted President Mohamed Bazoum.照片：萨姆·梅德尼克/美联社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001106229"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/vivian-salama" itemprop="url" rel="author">维维安·萨拉马</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 8 月 2 日晚上 9:45（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/state-department-orders-partial-evacuation-of-u-s-embassy-in-niger-48bcb7bd"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> WASHINGTON—The State Department ordered Wednesday the departure of nonemergency US government employees and eligible family members from Niger over concerns that tensions could escalate after <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-leaders-detain-ministers-party-officials-6ba1efa1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">the military junta detained the country&#39;s elected president</a> last week.</p><p>美国国务院更新了其警告，该警告此前曾警告美国公民因犯罪、恐怖主义和绑架而重新考虑前往尼日尔的旅行。目前尚不清楚有多少美国人居住在尼日尔，国务院表示正在评估可以采取哪些措施来确保所有美国人的安全。</p><p> “The Department of State is ordering the temporary departure of nonemergency US government personnel and eligible family members from the US Embassy in Niamey,” the Department said. “商业航班选择有限。我们更新了旅行警告以反映这一点，并通知美国公民，鉴于人员减少，我们只能向尼日尔的美国公民提供紧急援助。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-828747?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">美国国务院发言人表示，尼日尔首都尼亚美目前的局势不稳定但平静。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：ISSIFOU DJIBO/EPA/Shutterstock</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Earlier Wednesday, State Department spokesman Matthew Miller said that the safety and security of embassy personnel and US citizens overseas is the administration&#39;s highest priority and that the situation at present in Niger&#39;s capital is fluid but calm.</p><p> “我们不断监控现场事件，并根据保护我们人员的适当措施做出决定，”他说。</p><p> The State Department said that the embassy in Niamey remains open for limited emergency services to US citizens and that it would continuously re-examine the situation as security conditions permit.</p><p> While it wasn&#39;t immediately clear why the department changed course, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/west-african-leaders-threaten-force-against-niger-plotters-e046fae7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">a one-week deadline</a> imposed on Sunday by the 15-nation Economic Community of West African States for the military junta to cede power is approaching.欧盟表示，如果未能在最后期限前完成，将考虑进行军事干预，驱逐政变策划者并恢复这个广阔的撒哈拉国家的民主统治。</p><p> On Tuesday, European governments began evacuating their citizens from Niger after <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-general-declares-himself-leader-as-russian-mercenary-hails-coup-d47efa68?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">last week&#39;s coup</a> in the West African country triggered a tense standoff between <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/france-prepares-to-evacuate-european-citizens-from-coup-hit-niger-d46774af?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">Moscow&#39;s allies in the region</a> and countries that have worked more closely with the US and other Western powers. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-828749?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">从尼日尔撤离的欧洲人和美国人于周三抵达意大利。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：雷莫·卡西利/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>由尼日尔前殖民统治者法国领导的撤离行动表明，欧洲各国政府预计其公民在该国面临更高的风险，这对于美国打击萨赫勒地区伊斯兰武装分子的努力<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-upends-u-s-security-plans-in-west-africa-handing-russia-an-opportunity-8dcf6679?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">至关重要</a>。萨赫勒地区是撒哈拉以南的半干旱地带。 。</p><p> Last week, US Secretary of State Antony Blinken expressed support for Niger&#39;s president, Mohamed Bazoum, during a visit to Australia and warned that Washington could cut support to Niger if the military held on to power.然而，布林肯和其他美国官员并没有将尼日尔发生的事件描述为一场政变，根据美国法律，政变将立即冻结援助。</p><p>布林肯周三与巴祖姆进行了通话，这是自这位尼日尔领导人被软禁以来他与巴祖姆进行的几次通话之一。根据国务院的通报，布林肯重申了美国对“恢复民选政府”的承诺。他告诉巴祖姆，美国“致力于寻求和平解决方案，确保尼日尔仍然是该地区安全与发展的强大伙伴。”</p><p>自2012年以来，美国已花费超过5亿美元来建设和训练尼日尔武装部队。这个幅员辽阔的西非国家驻有美国无人机和美国突击队，他们除了进行训练外，还为尼日尔特种部队在<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/niger-coup-upends-u-s-security-plans-in-west-africa-handing-russia-an-opportunity-8dcf6679?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">打击叛乱分子的战斗任务</a>中提供建议。</p><p> On Saturday, the EU&#39;s foreign-policy chief,</p> Josep Borrell, said the bloc had frozen budgetary support as well as military assistance to Niger <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/apparent-coup-attempt-hits-u-s-ally-niger-e3efa36d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">in response to the rebellion</a> and would continue to recognize Bazoum as the country&#39;s legitimate president.<p></p><p>欧盟还在尼日尔派驻了培训团。此次冻结影响了该使命以及欧盟计划在 2021 年至 2024 年间向尼日尔预算和针对人口的项目提供的 5.03 亿欧元（约合 5.5 亿美元）的大部分资金。欧盟将继续向尼日尔提供援助。向尼日尔提供人道主义援助。</p><p>几天前，由于海地安全局势恶化，国务院下令非紧急人员撤离海地。</p><p>写信给 Vivian Salama： <a href="mailto:vivian.salama@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">vivian.salama@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 03 Aug 2023 01:45:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/state-department-orders-partial-evacuation-of-us-embassy-in-niger-48bcb7bd</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/state-department-orders-partial-evacuation-of-us-embassy-in-niger-48bcb7bd<author><![CDATA[Vivian Salama]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>社会/社区</category><category>叛乱</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>国际关系</category><category>人类迁徙</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>恐怖主义</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>社会</category><category>社区</category><category>叛乱</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>国际关系</category><category>人类迁徙</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>恐怖主义</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item></channel></rss>